To run this from the command line (the only option we support right now) enter something like the following:
python wallpaper_wrangler.py 1920 1080 3 2 1 1 input.jpg output.jpg
the arguments in order are:
the horizontal resolution of one monitor (1920)
the vertical resolution of one monitor (1080), 
the number of monitors comprising the horizontal dimension of your large display (3), 
the number of monitors comprising the vertical dimension of your large display (2),
the zero-based x coordinate of your primary monitor, where origin is considered to be the top left monitor (1),
the zero-based y coordinate of your primary monitor, where origin is considered to be the top left monitor (1),
the image that needs wrangling (to prevent the mangling),
the filename to which to write the wrangled image